I know logically they wont hate me or be mad at me or anything for simply writing made up stuff. And it's not like the characters or story is malicious or anything. It's just. You know. My feelings and thoughts are kind of driving it. Im nervous about it not living inside my head anymore. Umm I'm not really sure how to wrap this up into a coherent question. It's freaking me out, I'm starting to get bad feelings whenever I play because I know it won't be up to standards. I still want to be very good, but I don't want to end up losing what I love about music or hate playing. Do you have any advice to not let the pressures get to me but still succeed? I want to make great music, but I don't want to sell my happiness for it. Thank you <3

12.23.24  8:54 pm   Hope the holidays are going well for you.
Whenever asked about your favorite song (of yours), you answer that you'd rather make a new one to be your favorite. You've said that this is because you believe every song you make has to be made with the mentality that it'll be better than the song that came before it.
I wonder, though, by that logic, is the last song you'll make before retirement (if you plan to retire from making music at some point) the best song you'll ever make? Do you think you'd be satisfied with that song enough not to feel the urge to make another better one? If not, then does that mean that you'll probably keep making songs for the rest of your life and, therefore not really retire from music?
